   579тЖТ## Docs
   581тЖТDotenv exposes four functions:
   582тЖТ
      тЖТтАж
   587тЖТ### Config
   589тЖТ`config` will read your `.env` file, parse the contents, assign it to
   590тЖТ[`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env),
      тЖТтАж
   605тЖТ#### Options
   607тЖТ##### path
   609тЖТDefault: `path.resolve(process.cwd(), '.env')`
   610тЖТ
   611тЖТSpecify a custom path if your file containing environment variables is located elsewhere.
   612тЖТ
   613тЖТ```js
   614тЖТrequire('dotenv').config({ path: '/custom/path/to/.env' })
   615тЖТ```
   616тЖТ
   617тЖТBy default, `config` will look for a file called .env in the current working directory.
   618тЖТ
   619тЖТPass in multiple files as an array, and they will be parsed in order and combined with `process.env` (or `option.processEnv`, if set). The first value set for a variable will win, unless the `options.override` flag is set, in which case the last value set will win.  If a value already exists in `process.env` and the `options.override` flag is NOT set, no changes will be made to that value. 
   620тЖТ
   621тЖТ```js  
   622тЖТrequire('dotenv').config({ path: ['.env.local', '.env'] })
   623тЖТ```
   624тЖТ
   625тЖТ##### quiet
   627тЖТDefault: `false`
   628тЖТ
      тЖТтАж
   648тЖТ##### encoding
   650тЖТDefault: `utf8`
   651тЖТ
      тЖТтАж
   658тЖТ##### debug
   660тЖТDefault: `false`
   661тЖТ
      тЖТтАж
   668тЖТ##### override
   670тЖТDefault: `false`
   671тЖТ
      тЖТтАж
   678тЖТ##### processEnv
   680тЖТDefault: `process.env`
   681тЖТ
      тЖТтАж
   692тЖТ### Parse
   694тЖТThe engine which parses the contents of your file containing environment
   695тЖТvariables is available to use. It accepts a String or Buffer and will return
      тЖТтАж
   705тЖТ#### Options
   707тЖТ##### debug
   709тЖТDefault: `false`
   710тЖТ
   711тЖТTurn on logging to help debug why certain keys or values are not being set as you expect.
   712тЖТ
   713тЖТ```js
   714тЖТconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   715тЖТconst buf = Buffer.from('hello world')
   716тЖТconst opt = { debug: true }
   717тЖТconst config = dotenv.parse(buf, opt)
   718тЖТ// expect a debug message because the buffer is not in KEY=VAL form
   719тЖТ```
   720тЖТ
   721тЖТ### Populate
   723тЖТThe engine which populates the contents of your .env file to `process.env` is available for use. It accepts a target, a source, and options. This is useful for power users who want to supply their own objects.
   724тЖТ
      тЖТтАж
   748тЖТ#### options
   750тЖТ##### Debug
   752тЖТDefault: `false`
   753тЖТ
   754тЖТTurn on logging to help debug why certain keys or values are not being populated as you expect.
   755тЖТ
   756тЖТ##### override
   758тЖТDefault: `false`
   759тЖТ
